summary: Haircut Brothers from Goldenrod City’s Underground Tunnel. They can groom your Pokemon in order to raise its Happiness stat. ...
caption:
Haircut Brothers from Goldenrod City’s Underground Tunnel. They can groom your Pokemon in order to raise its Happiness stat.

They made an easy-to-miss cameo appearance in the anime’s EP158 “A Goldenrod Opportunity”. Interesting how the anime portrays them as twin brothers, while the game implies a notable age difference between them.

summary: Pokemon Card of the Day #1293: Milotic (Supreme Victors #SH7)
title: Pokemon Card of the Day #1293: Milotic (Supreme Victors #SH7)
body:
Milotic was one of the secret Shiny Pokemon in Supreme Victors, and it did have an interesting concept. It aimed to prevent taking damage by having no cards in the user’s hand, which was a bit of a price to say the least. Then again, being unable to take damage was really powerful despite there being ways around it, so it was only a matter of time before someone gave it a try.

80 HP on a Stage 1 was a bit low, and the +20 Lightning Weakness made it easier for Luxray GL to pick off Milotic. At least Milotic could retreat for just an Energy if it survived an attack.

Aqua Mirage was powerful but hard to use. If you had no cards in your hand, all damage done to Milotic by your opponent’s Pokemon was prevented. You had to be able to get rid of all of your cards in the first place, which could be tough considering it wasn’t hard to be stuck with an extra Evolution card of multiple Supporters, and then you were just kind of drawing off the top of your deck and hoping to keep this going. It wasn’t easy to pull off, but it was really annoying to face when it worked.

Dwindling Wave started off strong. 80 damage for 3 Energy was quite nice! 10 was taken off for each damage counter on Milotic, sadly, so Aqua Mirage was even more vital. A weakened Milotic was a useless Milotic.

Milotic had a strong Poke-Body, but it was so hard to use consistently that it wasn’t worth playing. That’s not to say that this card was useless, however. It was a pretty cool collector’s item.

summary: How do we evolve haunter in your rg project? Sorry if it's a silly question, I'm just curious
question: How do we evolve haunter in your rg project? Sorry if it's a silly question, I'm just curious
answer:
No problem! It’s written in the txt file what level it evolves at, I can’t remember the exact one? But yes it evolves by leveling up (this is v 2.0 only, btw).

As for the rest of the Pokemon that evolve by trading, if their evolutions are gen 2, then you can’t evolve them until you get the National Dex (i.e. Golbat, Poliwhirl, etc.)
